 Portrait of beautiful Caucasian woman in towel looking herself in the mirror and applying face cream. She is going through morning beauty routine in bathroom. Skin Care and Hygiene Here are morning afternoon and night daily routines to learn for that ageless and perfect skin glow. Morning:
Wash your face with a gentle cleanser to remove any dirt or oil that has accumulated overnight.
Apply a moisturizer with SPF to protect your skin from sun damage.
Eat a healthy breakfast that includes fruits and vegetables.
Cleanse your face with a gentle cleanser suitable for your skin type
Apply a light moisturizer to keep your skin hydrated
Drink a glass of water to rehydrate your skin Afternoon:
Drink plenty of water throughout the day to keep your skin hydrated.
Avoid touching your face with your hands to prevent transferring bacteria or oil to your skin.
Take a short walk or do some light exercise to improve blood flow to your skin.
Touch up your sunscreen as needed
Take a break from makeup if possible to let your skin breathe
Eat a healthy lunch that includes fruits and vegetables Night:
Remove makeup and cleanse your face before bedtime to remove any impurities and makeup.
Apply a retinol or other anti-ageing product to stimulate collagen production.
Get at least 7-8 hours of sleep to allow your skin time to repair itself.
Cleanse your face again to remove any makeup or impurities
Apply a night cream to nourish your skin while you sleep
Apply eye cream to prevent wrinkles and dark circles
Drink a glass of water before bed
Avoid eating heavy or greasy foods before bedtime These habits are suitable for all types of skin, but it’s important to remember that your skincare routine should be tailored to your specific skin type and concerns. Consult a dermatologist if you have any doubts or questions. In addition to these habits, it’s also important to maintain a healthy lifestyle, which includes eating a balanced diet, getting regular exercise, and avoiding smoking and excessive alcohol consumption. 